<p><strong>Canadian Drainage Terminology Evolution:</strong></p>

<p>The terminology differences reflect both historical development and regional preferences across Canada:</p>

<ul><li><strong>Weeping tile</strong>: Traditional Canadian term dating to early 1900s when clay tiles were used</li>
