<li><strong>Vapor barrier protection</strong>: Preserve existing moisture barriers where possible</li>

<p></ul><strong>Step 3: Excavation to Foundation Footing Level</strong></p>

<strong>Excavation Standards:</strong>
<ul><li><strong>Depth to footing</strong>: Typically 12-18" below existing floor</li>
<li><strong>Width consistency</strong>: Maintain uniform trench width</li>
<li><strong>Base preparation</strong>: Level and compact subgrade</li>
<li><strong>Wall exposure</strong>: Clean foundation wall for inspection</li>
<li><strong>Safety protocols</strong>: Shore unstable excavations</li>

</ul><strong>Foundation Inspection:</strong>
<ul><li><strong>Crack identification</strong>: Document and address structural issues</li>
<li><strong>Joint sealing</strong>: Repair cove joint separations</li>
