<li><strong>Moisture assessment</strong>: Identify active water entry points</li>

<p></ul><strong>Step 4: Professional Drainage System Installation</strong></p>

<strong>Base Preparation:</strong>
\`\`\`
Foundation Base Installation:
<li>Compact subgrade to 95% density</li>
<li>Install 4-6" gravel base (¾" clean stone)</li>
<li>Level base with laser level for consistent slope</li>
<li>Verify minimum 1% grade throughout system</li>
<li>Create smooth transitions at corners and connections</li>
\`\`\`

<strong>Pipe Installation:</strong>
\`\`\`
Perforated Pipe Installation:
<li>Use rigid PVC pipe (4" minimum diameter)</li>
<li>Install with holes facing down (contrary to common belief)</li>
<li>Maintain consistent slope using laser level</li>
<li>Secure pipe position with gravel support</li>
<li>Connect sections with approved fittings</li>
<li>Run continuous to sump basin location</li>
\`\`\`

<strong>Filter System Installation:</strong>
\`\`\`
Gravel and Fabric System:
<li>Surround pipe with 6-8" additional gravel</li>
<li>Install non-woven geotextile filter fabric</li>
<li>Wrap entire gravel bed completely</li>
<li>Overlap fabric seams minimum 6"</li>
<li>Secure fabric to prevent displacement</li>
\`\`\`

